{
  "text": "These views shift the tool-centric conception of technology in which the role of AI has been positioned as a powerful learning tool to effectively attain the learning goals predetermined, to the agent-centric approach driven by post-humanist theory such as Actor-Network Theory (ANT), highlighting the interplay of humans and technology and acknowledge both students and AI are agents in their own right and transact all learning activities with each other in mutually engaging and supportive way (Kim & Cho, 2023)."
}